# Patch 0024 — Kavacha Customization Studio (about:studio): the Visual Browser
# Builder (ROADMAP Phase 3 "Visual Browser Builder"; ADR 0009).
#
# WHAT: registers about:studio as a JS nsIAboutModule (KavachaAboutStudio.sys.mjs
# + components.conf) that resolves to a privileged chrome page
# (chrome://browser/content/kavacha-studio/studio.html). The page redesigns the
# browser WITHOUT CSS: a Layout tab (tab orientation, sidebar side/width,
# density, toolbar) driving KavachaLayoutEngine (patch 0022), and a Themes tab
# listing + switching theme packages via KavachaThemeEngine (patch 0023). Every
# control writes through those engines' public APIs, which already apply live to
# every window — so the "preview" is the real browser. Palette: "Open
# Customization Studio".
#
# WHY A JS ABOUT-MODULE (not a Gecko C++ redirector edit): about:studio needs a
# stable typed URL and parent-process chrome privileges (IS_SECURE_CHROME_UI,
# like about:preferences) so studio.js can call the chrome singletons directly.
# The modern JS nsIAboutModule pattern (mirrors
# engine/browser/components/newtab/AboutNewTabRedirector.sys.mjs) gives both
# without touching engine C++ (MASTER_PLAN Principle 1). A new
# src/zen/kavacha-studio/ overlay dir carries the module, its components.conf,
# the page assets (jar.inc.mn), and moz.build — wired via src/zen/moz.build DIRS
# and zen-assets.jar.inc.mn.
#
# NOT BUILD-VERIFIED: authored against the post-0023 tree; hunks reconstructed
# there. Run `git -C browser/zen-upstream apply --check` + a Marionette pass
# (open about:studio, toggle each control, confirm chrome updates, switch theme)
# before marking the ROADMAP item verified. Adds src/zen/kavacha-studio/*;
# touches src/zen/moz.build, zen-assets.jar.inc.mn, zen-command-palette.ftl,
# KavachaCommandRegistry.sys.mjs. Applies on top of 0023.
